  <description type="morphology">Plants often woody at base; finely stellate-pubescent. Stems: usually several, 1–5 dm. Basal leaves: petiole 0.5–3(–4) cm, blade spatulate to obovate or lanceolate, (2.5–)4–8(–12) × 0.5–1.5(–2.5) cm, base cuneate to attenuate, margins entire, repand, or sinuate-dentate, apex acute or obtuse, surfaces densely pubescent. Cauline leaves: blade oblanceolate to linear. Racemes slightly elongated in fruit. Fruiting pedicels (3–)4.5–10(–13) mm. Flowers: sepals yellowish, scarious at margins, finely pubescent, 1.5–2.3 × 0.5–1 mm; petals 3–6 × 1–2.5 mm, attenuate to clawlike base; filaments with basal wing or appendage to 0.5 mm, 1–2 mm; anthers 0.3–0.5 mm. Fruits divaricate-ascending, broadly obovate to orbicular, flattened, strongly latiseptate, 3.5–9 mm in diam.; style 0.5–1.5(–2.5) mm. Seeds winged throughout, 2–3 mm diam.; wing 0.3–1.1 mm wide. 2n = 16.</description>
